President Obama released a statement recognizing the celebration of Hanukkah and highlighting its significance. He emphasized the message of freedom and hope that Hanukkah represents, as well as the ability to overcome challenges. The President also mentioned the symbolism of the menorah and the miracle of the oil lasting for eight nights. He encouraged people to do what is right, appreciate the miracles in their lives, and share those miracles with others. The statement concludes with a holiday greeting from the President's family.